              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A <html:strong>structure</html:strong> for a language is a set of values, together with an account of how every connective in the language acts on those values.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <html:p>And given a structure, we can say what it takes to be a <html:strong>valuation</html:strong> in that structure:</html:p>
