              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A <html:strong>valuation</html:strong> in a structure for a language is a function from sentences of the language to values in the structure, where the value of every compound sentence in the language is related to the values of its components in the way the structure indicates.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <html:p>(Note that since <html:em>any</html:em> such function is a valuation, that means that valuations are not restricted at all when it comes to the values they assign to atomic sentences.)</html:p>
