            <html:p>         In giving a structure via tables like this, there's no need to separately specify the set of values, since you can read those off the edges of the tables.
        By packaging everything up into a structure in this way, we make it easy to change from one structure to another, to think about different kinds of valuations we might want to draw on, beyond just Boolean ones.
        In a moment, we'll look at a few other example structures, besides this Boolean one.
        But first, I want to look a bit at some uses of Boolean valuations.</html:p>
